content: What kind of flowers do you like, ,@,stagmetanoia,? ,https://,twitter.com/narinstwitt/st,atus/906886256830771201, ,…
May i suggest the purple spotted white phalaenopsis orchids,pic.twitter.com/QjLN7vvNJx
Also known as the blood splatter orchid. I wonder why

I’ve never seen those before. They’re beautiful.
I also like amaryllises and hydrangeas. Had a wild few bushes back in Louisiana.
Those orchids are exquisite. Amaryllis are lovely and structural, and hydrangea are...old-fashioned. They suit you.
The black rose blooms only in one place: Halfeti, in Turkey. I wonder if we could obtain some for our wedding.
Really? Of course we could. I’m assuming you would know how to go about doing that.
